Deputy
Chief Justice Raymond Zondo is handing over the State Capture Commission of
Inquiry to President Cyril Ramaphosa. Ramaphosa
issued a statement on Monday that he would receive the first part of the final
report of the Zondo Commission on Tuesday. The president
said the final report will be submitted to him in three parts. The
handover of the first part of the report will take place at the Union Buildings
in Pretoria at 3.30pm today, 4 January. The second
part is expected to be handed over at the end of this month and the final part
at the end of next month. 